/span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.2pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">As a group of independent schools and academies, we </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">see first hand the much greater focus independent schools have on attainment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> at A level than at GCSE and in relation to destinations</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">It is critical that academies are able to have a similar focus if </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">we are to have major impact on offering the least advantaged better opportunity to progress to university. Our academies are increa</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">sing their focus on this age group, and this year we are sending more academy students to Russell Group universities than ever before.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">W</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">re celebrating Oxbridge successes at three academies for whom </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">this</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> would have been </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">unimaginable </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in the past.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:130%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 3